  N5 --> N6[PB: CWB Lifecycle - Human review for exceptions and present KPIs]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Improved forecast accuracy and explainability, reduced stockouts and excess inventory across supplier-plant-DC tiers, lower working capital and tighter COGS, and auditable human-in-the-loop exceptions when needed]
  N4 -->|Forecast accuracy (MAPE) for a segmen...| B1[Trigger automated retrain using alternative features or raise Data Science subprocess; hold automated writeback for affected SKUs and create CWB for planner review]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Models retrained and validated; prevents propagation of poor forecasts into supply chain; human approval required before writeback]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Supplier lead times or lot sizes chan...| B2[Process Builder applies constrained optimization and switches to supply-constrained plan; notify procurement and suppliers via Notification node]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Adjusted plans prioritize available capacity, reduce stockout risk, and engage procurement for remediation]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Planner overrides forecast recommenda...| B3[Capture override via CWB Lifecycle, log rationale, and suspend automatic writeback for that SKU until next governance window]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Human-inspected changes are auditable and isolate manual decisions from automated pipeline while preserving data lineage]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]